defs.docs: Epoch-based memory reclamation.

defs.name: CompareAndSetError
defs.docs: The error returned on failed compare-and-set operation.

defs.name: current
defs.docs: The value in the atomic pointer at the time of the failed operation.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: The new value, which the operation failed to store.

defs.name: CompareAndSetOrdering
defs.docs: Memory orderings for compare-and-set operations.

defs.name: success
defs.docs: The ordering of the operation when it succeeds.

defs.name: failure
defs.docs: The ordering of the operation when it fails.

defs.name: Atomic
defs.docs: An atomic pointer that can be safely shared between threads.

defs.name: null
defs.docs: Returns a new null atomic pointer.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Allocates `value` on the heap and returns a new atomic pointer pointing to it.

defs.name: load
defs.value: fn <'g> (&self, ord: Ordering, _: &'g Guard) -> Shared<'g, T>
defs.docs: Loads a `Shared` from the atomic pointer.

defs.name: load_consume
defs.docs: Loads a `Shared` from the atomic pointer using a "consume" memory ordering.

defs.name: store
defs.value: fn <'g, P> (&self, new: P, ord: Ordering) -> ()
defs.docs: Stores a `Shared` or `Owned` pointer into the atomic pointer.

defs.name: swap
defs.value: fn <'g, P> (&self, new: P, ord: Ordering, _: &'g Guard) -> Shared<'g, T>
defs.docs:
Stores a `Shared` or `Owned` pointer into the atomic pointer, returning the previous
 `Shared`.

defs.name: compare_and_set
defs.value: fn <'g, O, P> (&self, current: Shared<T>, new: P, ord: O, _: &'g Guard) -> Result<Shared<'g, T>, CompareAndSetError<'g, T, P>>
defs.docs:
Stores the pointer `new` (either `Shared` or `Owned`) into the atomic pointer if the current
 value is the same as `current`. The tag is also taken into account, so two pointers to the
 same object, but with different tags, will not be considered equal.

defs.name: compare_and_set_weak
defs.value: fn <'g, O, P> (&self, current: Shared<T>, new: P, ord: O, _: &'g Guard) -> Result<Shared<'g, T>, CompareAndSetError<'g, T, P>>
defs.docs:
Stores the pointer `new` (either `Shared` or `Owned`) into the atomic pointer if the current
 value is the same as `current`. The tag is also taken into account, so two pointers to the
 same object, but with different tags, will not be considered equal.

defs.name: fetch_and
defs.value: fn <'g> (&self, val: usize, ord: Ordering, _: &'g Guard) -> Shared<'g, T>
defs.docs: Bitwise "and" with the current tag.

defs.name: fetch_or
defs.value: fn <'g> (&self, val: usize, ord: Ordering, _: &'g Guard) -> Shared<'g, T>
defs.docs: Bitwise "or" with the current tag.

defs.name: fetch_xor
defs.value: fn <'g> (&self, val: usize, ord: Ordering, _: &'g Guard) -> Shared<'g, T>
defs.docs: Bitwise "xor" with the current tag.

defs.name: into_owned
defs.docs: Takes ownership of the pointee.

defs.name: Pointer
defs.docs: A trait for either `Owned` or `Shared` pointers.

defs.name: into_usize
defs.docs: Returns the machine representation of the pointer.

defs.name: from_usize
defs.docs: Returns a new pointer pointing to the tagged pointer `data`.

defs.name: Owned
defs.docs: An owned heap-allocated object.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Allocates `value` on the heap and returns a new owned pointer pointing to it.

defs.name: from_raw
defs.docs: Returns a new owned pointer pointing to `raw`.

defs.name: into_shared
defs.docs: Converts the owned pointer into a [`Shared`].

defs.name: into_box
defs.docs: Converts the owned pointer into a `Box`.

defs.name: tag
defs.docs: Returns the tag stored within the pointer.

defs.name: with_tag
defs.docs:
Returns the same pointer, but tagged with `tag`. `tag` is truncated to be fit into the
 unused bits of the pointer to `T`.

defs.name: Shared
defs.docs: A pointer to an object protected by the epoch GC.

defs.name: null
defs.docs: Returns a new null pointer.

defs.name: is_null
defs.docs: Returns `true` if the pointer is null.

defs.name: as_raw
defs.docs: Converts the pointer to a raw pointer (without the tag).

defs.name: deref
defs.docs: Dereferences the pointer.

defs.name: deref_mut
defs.docs: Dereferences the pointer.

defs.name: as_ref
defs.docs: Converts the pointer to a reference.

defs.name: into_owned
defs.docs: Takes ownership of the pointee.

defs.name: tag
defs.docs: Returns the tag stored within the pointer.

defs.name: with_tag
defs.docs:
Returns the same pointer, but tagged with `tag`. `tag` is truncated to be fit into the
 unused bits of the pointer to `T`.

defs.name: Collector
defs.docs: An epoch-based garbage collector.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new collector.

defs.name: register
defs.docs: Registers a new handle for the collector.

defs.name: LocalHandle
defs.docs: A handle to a garbage collector.

defs.name: pin
defs.docs: Pins the handle.

defs.name: is_pinned
defs.docs: Returns `true` if the handle is pinned.

defs.name: collector
defs.docs: Returns the `Collector` associated with this handle.

defs.name: Guard
defs.docs: A guard that keeps the current thread pinned.

defs.name: defer
defs.docs:
Stores a function so that it can be executed at some point after all currently pinned
 threads get unpinned.

defs.name: defer_unchecked
defs.docs:
Stores a function so that it can be executed at some point after all currently pinned
 threads get unpinned.

defs.name: defer_destroy
defs.docs:
Stores a destructor for an object so that it can be deallocated and dropped at some point
 after all currently pinned threads get unpinned.

defs.name: flush
defs.docs:
Clears up the thread-local cache of deferred functions by executing them or moving into the
 global cache.

defs.name: repin
defs.docs: Unpins and then immediately re-pins the thread.

defs.name: repin_after
defs.value: fn <F, R> (&mut self, f: F) -> R
defs.docs: Temporarily unpins the thread, executes the given function and then re-pins the thread.

defs.name: collector
defs.docs: Returns the `Collector` associated with this guard.

defs.name: unprotected
defs.docs: Returns a reference to a dummy guard that allows unprotected access to [`Atomic`]s.

defs.name: pin
defs.docs: Pins the current thread.

defs.name: is_pinned
defs.docs: Returns `true` if the current thread is pinned.

defs.name: default_collector
defs.docs: Returns the default global collector.
